---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Mattias Olsson — Unity developer building WebGL games from cozy companions to deep-sea survival."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-white">About</h1>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-muted">
      <p>
        I'm <strong class="text-white">Mattias Olsson</strong>, a Unity developer
        who builds small games with strong moods — cozy forest companions, math-driven
        space combat, and deep-sea horde survival. I like tight loops, readable mechanics,
        and projects that feel good in a five-minute browser session.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each game ships to <strong class="text-white">Unity Play</strong> as WebGL.
        <strong class="text-white">Playframe</strong> is the portfolio layer on top:
        context, screenshots, and embedded playback so you can try everything without
        leaving the site.
      </p>
      <p>
        Right now I'm especially interested in touch-friendly companion games and
        arcade experiments that mix learning with pressure. If a project clicks, I
        push it from prototype to something you can actually play in a tab.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/mattiasolssondev"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="font-medium text-accent transition-colors hover:text-white"
        >
          GitHub ↗
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
